 Job Summary
 The Business Operations-Analyst will join the sales incentive compensation team and own the execution of sales incentive plans for the sales teams. We are looking for an experienced individual who values accuracy, thrives in the details, uses critical thinking to find solutions, can prioritize work to meet deadlines and has an appreciation for process efficiencies. This role is the key point of contact for the sales organization for their incentive plans and must build relationships as a trusted partner. As a member of a global business operations team, this person must possess the desire and ability to work well in a fast-paced and complex environment where taking ownership and initiative is the foundation for success.
 Job Description
 Closely partner with various departments across FICO including Sales Leaders, Regional Sales Operations, HR, Payroll, Accounting, Finance, Legal and IT to align and support the implementation and administration of sales incentive plans.
 Maintain a thorough understanding of the incentive plan component mechanics to ensure payments are accurate and in compliance with each participantâ€™s sales incentive plan document.
 Support the annual incentive planning process including the development of quotas, territories and plan structure for each plan participant. Deploy the assignments within Xactly and distribute incentive plan documents.
 Execute the calculation of incentive payments using the incentive compensation management tool Xactly Incent. Administer and manage day-to-day operations in the tool required to process a participantâ€™s payment.
 Create and produce reports to support control procedures required for audit compliance for payroll submission of incentive payments.
 Track, research and resolve commission inquiries and disputes and provide solutions to Management to resolve complex commission exceptions as needed.
 Support the development and execution of SPIF programs.
 Provide enablement to plan participants in the use of Xactly including delivery of sales incentive plan documents, system navigation and calculation inquiries. Evaluate the Xactly tool interface to ensure it continues to meet the needs of incentive reporting for the end user.
 Generate quota and incentive attainment reports and other ad hoc sales performance reporting as requested. Produce reports that supply insight and guidance to enhance sales productivity.
 Provide recommendations for operational efficiencies and process improvements and assist in change initiatives from requirements gathering through adoption.
 Communicate effectively and professionally in all forms of communication with internal and external customers.
